ation over Time: A Situated Change Perspective\" in Information Systems Research, 7(1), 63-92. Osborne, D. and Gaebler, T. (1992), Reinventing Government: How the Entrepreneurial Spirit is Transforming the Public Sector, Addison-Wesley Publishing Pascale, R. (1999) Extract from Complexity and the unconscious, in J. Henry, Creativity ,Innovation and Change Media Book, Milton Keynes: Open University Press, pp. 9-10. Pearson, G. (1989) \u2018Promoting entrepreneurship in large companies', Long Range Planning, Vol. 22, No. 3, pp. 87-97. Pitts, D., W., and Fernandez, S. (2006), \u2018Under what conditions do public managers favour and pursue organisational change?\u2019, Andrew Young School of Policy Studies, Research Paper Series, Working Paper 06-19, March 2006 Santayana, G. (1905) The Life of Reason, Volume 1 29 Senge, P. (1990), The Fifth Discipline: The art and practice of the learning organisation, Doubleday, New York Senge, P. (1999) The Dance of Change, Currency Doubleday, New York Senge, P.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "1caf7ecb-715c-4b68-ab6b-64f57f07a8c0": {"__data__": {"id_": "1caf7ecb-715c-4b68-ab6b-64f57f07a8c0", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/institutional-reform-and-change-management", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Institutional Reform and Change Management", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/institutional-reform-and-change-management", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "cb04b2c5d58d5dcd07f11b21f44